T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 321
EP  - 335
VL  - 13
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper analyzes the pattern of periodic reinvestments in depreciable assets when the amount of reinvestment in each period is set equal to the amount of depreciation for the period and derives a constant to which the periodic investments converge. The expression for the constant which depends upon the depreciation method is then interpreted in terms of the firm's investment and financing policy as well as its growth rate.
